{{Quote|I pledge myself to you, Qui-Gon.|Tahl, to Qui-Gon Jinn|<ref name="The Ties That Bind" />}}
'''Tahl''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Noorian]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]], a [[Jedi librarian/Legends|librarian]] of the [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Jedi Archives]], and was also a close friend of [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]], with whom she fell in love. She was also the master of [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Bant Eerin/Legends|Bant Eerin]]. During a mission on [[Melida/Daan/Legends|Melida/Daan]], she was blinded in a [[Prison/Legends|prison]]. However, her improved hearing and [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitivity]] helped her get back on her feet.

==Biography==
===Early life===
{{Quote|A good match."<br />"It would have been better if I'd won."<br />"Don't you ever give up?"<br />"Never.|[[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]] and Tahl, after [[Exhibition Day]]|<ref name="The Death of Hope" />}}
Brought to the [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] at the advanced age of 6, the young [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] girl was permitted to start her [[Jedi training/Legends|training]] at the [[Jedi academy|Temple academy]], learning the ways of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. A close friend of [[Jedi Initiate/Legends|Initiate]] [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]], the two would maintain a relationship through their apprenticeships and as [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]].<ref name="TCSWE">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> During [[Exhibition Day]] of [[82 BBY/Legends|82 BBY]], while she and Qui-Gon Jinn were still Initiates, she had won every last dueling match up until she had defeated [[Clee Rhara]]. She was pitted in the final round against Jinn. They knew each other's strengths, which made the exceedingly long duel very interesting to all the spectators around them. Even [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] came to watch. In the end, Tahl momentarily slipped on her own sweat and Jinn knocked her to the ground, holding the blade of his [[Training lightsaber/Legends|training lightsaber]] inches away from her to signal his victory.<ref name="The Death of Hope" />

Having constructed her own blue-bladed [[Tahl's lightsaber|lightsaber]] and training independently as a [[Jedi Consular|Consular]], Jedi Tahl specialized as a [[Jedi Researcher|researcher]] and [[Lore Keeper]] and could always be found close to the [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Temple Archives]]. However, Tahl still took assignments from the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]].<ref name="The Death of Hope" /> She and Jinn also became friends with [[Didi Oddo]], who ran a [[Dex's Diner/Legends|cafe]] on Coruscant.<ref name="The Deadly Hunter">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Deadly Hunter]]''</ref>

===Jedi Master===
[[File:Qui-Gon_and_Tahl.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Qui-Gon Jinn and Tahl as Jedi Masters]]
After both Tahl and Jinn achieved the rank of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]], the High Council encouraged them to take [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]]. While Master Jinn successfully trained [[Feemor]] and begun the tutelage of a young man named [[Xanatos]], Master Tahl still refused to take a student. In [[53 BBY/Legends|53 BBY]], the High Council assigned Tahl as steward of the orphaned Padawan [[Orykan Tamarik]] and dispatched the duo to [[Telos IV]], along with Master Jinn and Padawan Xanatos. While Jinn and his student were to investigate the mysterious death of [[High Priestess/Legends|High Priestess]] [[Liora]], Master Tahl was tasked with recovering the last of the [[Holocron/Legends|holocrons]] from the Order's abandoned [[Telosian Jedi Academy|academy]] on the world.<ref name="Dark Side 1" />

After collecting several volumes of text and the remaining holocrons, Master Tahl departed from the Telosian Archives building and stumbled upon a secret meeting in an exterior courtyard. One of the men, dressed in the garb of an [[Antarian Rangers/Legends|Antarian Ranger]], attacked Tahl upon seeing her; though Tahl gave chase all three men escaped.<ref name="Dark Side 2">[[Jedi — The Dark Side 2|''Jedi — The Dark Side'' 2]]</ref> Reporting this news to Jinn, Tahl later attempted to meet with him but a riot interrupted her. The riot, a cover for a group of insurgents to infiltrate the palace grounds, claimed the life of Princess [[Nason]]. When the riot was quelled,<ref name="Dark Side 3" /> Master Tahl informed the other Jedi that the Council had reassigned her, sending her to the [[Landor system/Legends|Landor system]] to apprehend the [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] who had captured [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Stieg Wa]].<ref name="Dark Side 4">[[Jedi — The Dark Side 4|''Jedi — The Dark Side'' 4]]</ref>

Years later, in [[47 BBY/Legends|47 BBY]], both Tahl and Jinn were dispatched to the planet [[New Apsolon/Legends|Apsolon]] as supervisors of the first free elections held on the world. While there, Tahl developed a close bond with the twin daughters of the people's' hero [[Ewane]]: [[Eritha]] and [[Alani]]. As a symbol of the democratization of Apsolon, the planet was renamed New Apsolon; Tahl reluctantly left the planet along with Jinn, as she wanted to stay to ensure the planet was stable.<ref name="The Ties That Bind" />

===Blindness===
By [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]], Tahl was sent to act as a peacemaker to the broken world of [[Melida/Daan/Legends|Melida/Daan]], where the [[Melida/Legends|Melida]] and [[Daan (people)/Legends|Daan]] people were murdering each other. She was caught in the battle and sustained injuries that caused her to lose her sight. A white scar had crossed all the way from her left eyebrow to her chin. As she was unable to free herself from Melida captivity, Qui-Gon Jinn and his new Padawan, [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], were sent to rescue her.<ref name="The Defenders of the Dead" /> Upon returning to Coruscant, Tahl was assigned [[2JTJ|TooJay]], a [[2JTJ personal navigation droid]] by [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] to assist her in her blindness; though she became more of a bother than a help.<ref name="TUP">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Uncertain Path]]''</ref>

Master Tahl was not greatly affected by her blindness, as she had an immense knowledge of galactic history, politics, and the backstory of practically everything and anything going on in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. Remaining at the Temple, Tahl kept herself useful by assisting Jedi before they departed on missions, giving them detailed backgrounds on planets and species they might encounter. When the Temple was vandalized and an attempt on Master Yoda's life was made, Tahl worked with Master Jinn to try to uncover the perpetrator. With the addition of several thefts, which included [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] and the [[Healing Crystals of Fire]], Tahl and Jinn began officially investigating the [[Incident at the Jedi Temple|incident]] and, with the aid of [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] Initiate [[Bant Eerin/Legends|Bant Eerin]], discovered that [[Bruck Chun]], a promising senior Jedi student, was the robber.<ref name="TUP" /> Later, when Xanatos was revealed to be the mastermind of the chaos, Tahl did what she could to discover what he was after: [[Crystalline vertex/Legends|crystalline vertex]] stored in the Temple's [[Treasury room]].<ref name="TCP">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Captive Temple]]''</ref> Once the Temple was secure, she helped trace Xanatos' company, the [[Offworld Mining Corporation]], to Telos IV, prompting Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi to [[Mission to Telos (44 BBY)|travel]] there.<ref name="DOR">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Day of Reckoning]]''</ref>

Following Eerin's display of courage during the Temple incident, Tahl selected the young girl as her Padawan; though she regularly left her behind to go on short missions of her own. This upset the members of the High Council as well as Jinn, with whom she had several arguments about the matter.<ref name="The Ties That Bind" /> Indeed, Tahl would accompany Jinn without her Padawan in [[42 BBY/Legends|42 BBY]] when the pair worked together to uncover a saboteur in Master [[Clee Rhara]]'s flight system on [[Centax-2/Legends|Centax-2]]. Uncovering the saboteur, using the alias of long deceased [[Tarrence Chenati]], the pair were too late to save the school from having its funding cut.<ref name="Deceptions">''[[Jedi Apprentice Special Edition: Deceptions]]''</ref>

===Return to New Apsolon and death===
{{Quote|Let my last moment be this one.|Tahl's final words|<ref name="The Death of Hope" />}}
[[File:Tahl_death.jpg|thumb|right|260px|Tahl on her deathbed, with Qui-Gon Jinn by her side]]
In [[41 BBY/Legends|41 BBY]] Tahl received a call of help from the twins Eritha and Alani of New Apsolon, as their father Ewane was murdered after being re-elected [[Supreme Governor]]. She answered the call for help and went alone to the world, despite Master Jinn's objections. Upon arriving on the world she accepted the twins' request to go undercover in the former secret police called the [[Absolutes]], now outlawed and trying to oust the planet's democratic government. As Tahl didn't report back to the High Council after several weeks, Master Jinn grew concerned and decided to go looking for her, despite the disapproval from the Council. The Jedi Master and Padawan Kenobi managed to find Tahl and helped her complete the mission. During their struggles, Master Jinn pledged his life to her, and she did the same to him, speaking aloud the feelings they had long held for each other. Little time had passed before Tahl's undercover status was discovered and she was kidnapped by [[Balog (Human)|Balog]], the Chief Security Controller who had pretended to assist the Jedi.<ref name="The Ties That Bind" /> Chief Balog kept her in a [[sensory deprivation containment device]], injecting a drug that slowly drained her of her strength.<ref name="The Death of Hope" />

Upon discovering their betrayal, Jinn and Kenobi began a full-scale chase of Chief Balog in the process of rescuing Tahl. When they finally found her, she was still alive, but the injuries she had suffered while in captivity were too severe, and she soon succumbed to her fatal injuries. This loss, magnified by Jinn's close relationship to her, drove him to the edge of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]].<ref name="The Death of Hope" /> Bent on seeking revenge, Jinn hunted down Balog and was prepared to execute him for his heinous acts. However, before Jinn could deliver the fatal blow to Balog's chest, Tahl's voice came to him warning him not to. He regained control of his emotions and didn't kill Balog, instead delivering Balog and the twins to the authorities.<ref name="The Call to Vengeance">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Call to Vengeance]]''</ref>

===Legacy===
Prior to Tahl's [[Death/Legends|death]] on [[New Apsolon/Legends|New Apsolon]], she was kidnapped by [[Chief of Security/Legends|Chief of Security]] and Absolutist [[Balog (Human)|Balog]]. When [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]] and his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] sensed something was wrong, they found an empty room and [[Tahl's lightsaber]] in a small bin. The lightsaber would briefly remain with Jinn, but was later passed down to Kenobi, whose [[Obi-Wan Kenobi's first lightsaber/Legends|own weapon]] was recharging. The young Padawan promised to keep it safe. When Tahl's body was taken to the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] for a [[Jedi funeral/Legends|funeral]], this lightsaber was presumably destroyed.

==Powers and abilities==
{{Quote|Balog may be head of security, but he's no match for Tahl. Even without her lightsaber.|Qui-Gon Jinn comments on the prowess of Tahl's skills|<ref name="The Death of Hope" />}}
[[File:SWJediDarkSide2.jpg|thumb|Tahl using her blue lightsaber to fend off her attackers on [[Telos IV]].]]
Tahl was highly capable at [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]]. Because she had been renowned for her gymnastics, she may have been a practitioner of [[Form IV/Legends|Form IV]]. She could come at her opponents with either a twist in one angle or a reversal on the other. Whenever she appeared to be tired out, she would draw out a fresh reserve of strength. Qui-Gon Jinn noted her to be of having greater agility than him. She was also capable at unarmed combat, as noted when she wrestled with a [[Zeku]] at a [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] while undercover.<ref name="The Death of Hope" /> Even after being blinded, Tahl could still manage to use a lightsaber in combat.<ref name="Deceptions" /> Tahl was a great lightsaber duelist, on par with Qui-Gon Jinn, one of the most skilled masters of Ataru, Form IV, at that time and era.

==Behind the scenes==
''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' misstates her death as [[39 BBY/Legends|39 BBY]].

